## Project Overview

**Classes (5):** `fist`, `open palm`, `peace`, `thumbs down`, `thumbs up`

**Final model:** YOLOv8n, trained on a custom dataset of 311 self-collected and annotated images, achieving **0.969 mAP50** and **0.937 precision** on the validation set.

---

## Assignment 1 — Dataset Creation

- **Total images collected:** 311 (exceeds the 300-image minimum)
- **Sources:** Self-collected across multiple people, to maximize variety within the available time
- **Variation included:**
  - Different backgrounds (plain walls, cluttered rooms, varied colors)
  - Different lighting conditions (bright, dim, natural, artificial)
  - Different viewing angles and hand rotations
  - Partial occlusions and varied hand-to-camera distances (scale variation)

### Dataset Split

| Split | Ratio | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Train | ~70% | Model training |
| Validation | ~20% | Hyperparameter tuning / mid-training evaluation |
| Test | ~10% | Final held-out evaluation |

Split was performed and documented via Roboflow during dataset versioning, and exported in YOLOv8 format with the ratio preserved.

---

## Assignment 2 — Annotation

- **Tool used:** Roboflow (bounding box annotation, class labeling, dataset versioning/export)
- **Process:** Every image was manually annotated with a tight bounding box around the visible hand gesture. An initial annotation pass used boxes that were too loose (including wrist/forearm/background); the dataset was re-annotated with corrected, tightly-fitted bounding boxes to improve model precision.

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Number of Images | 311 |
| Number of Classes | 5 |
| Classes | fist, open palm, peace, thumbs down, thumbs up |
| Annotation Format | YOLO (normalized `class x_center y_center width height` per image) |

---

## Assignment 3 — Model Training

**Framework:** Ultralytics YOLOv8 (trained in Google Colab, Tesla T4 GPU)

**Final training configuration:**

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Base model | `yolov8n.pt` (pretrained, transfer learning) |
| Epochs (set / actual via early stopping) | 100 / ~69 |
| Image size (imgsz) | 640 |
| Batch size | 16 |
| Learning rate (lr0) | 0.01 (optimizer auto-selected AdamW) |
| Patience (early stopping) | 20 |

Multiple training runs were conducted while iterating on the dataset and hyperparameters — see [Assignment 7](#assignment-7--experiments) for the full experiment log.

---

## Assignment 4 — Evaluation

**Final model validation results:**

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Precision | 0.937 |
| Recall | 0.907 |
| mAP50 | 0.969 |
| mAP50-95 | 0.668 |

**Per-class results:**

| Class | Precision | Recall | mAP50 | mAP50-95 |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| fist | 1.000 | 0.856 | 0.954 | 0.658 |
| open palm | 0.929 | 0.917 | 0.984 | 0.682 |
| peace | 0.904 | 0.900 | 0.978 | 0.588 |
| thumbs down | 0.872 | 1.000 | 0.995 | 0.833 |
| thumbs up | 0.982 | 0.864 | 0.934 | 0.578 |

Confusion matrix and sample prediction images are included in `/docs/evaluation/`.

**Strengths:** `thumbs down` and `open palm` are detected almost perfectly. Overall precision/recall balance is strong across all 5 classes with no major outliers.

**Weaknesses:** `thumbs up` has the lowest mAP50-95, indicating slightly less precise bounding box localization compared to other classes — a good candidate for additional targeted training data in future iterations.

