## Assignment 7 — Experiments

Four+ experiments were conducted and documented:

| # | Experiment | Summary |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Different epoch values | Early stopping consistently converged between 40-70 epochs depending on dataset version |
| 2 | Different image sizes | 640 imgsz outperformed 512 imgsz, matching real-world inference resolution |
| 3 | Augmented vs. non-augmented training | Augmentation reduced precision/mAP50 across three independent tests — non-augmented data consistently performed better on this dataset size |
| 4 | Different YOLO model sizes (n / s / m) | YOLOv8n outperformed both YOLOv8s and YOLOv8m on mAP50 and mAP50-95, while being smaller and faster — model capacity was not the bottleneck |

📄 Full experiment log and analysis: [`/docs/model_comparison_report.docx`](./docs/model_comparison_report.docx)

